Fix a genuine type bug that modern clang (Xcode 26) rejects.

nt/disable_audio.c defines DriverCallback() with its hDev parameter typed
HANDLE16 (unsigned short), but the prototype in nt/linux_audio.h types it
HWAVEOUT (void*, via nt/playaudd.h). Older compilers tolerated the pointer
vs. short mismatch; clang errors with "conflicting types for 'DriverCallback'".
The parameter is unused (audio is disabled), so match the definition to the
prototype. This is the only genuine source fix needed to build on Apple.

--- a/src/dapi/src/nt/disable_audio.c
+++ b/src/dapi/src/nt/disable_audio.c
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@
 }

-BOOL16 DriverCallback(void (*dwCallBack)(void *, unsigned int, unsigned int, long int, long int), UINT16 uFlags, HANDLE16 hDev,
+BOOL16 DriverCallback(void (*dwCallBack)(void *, unsigned int, unsigned int, long int, long int), UINT16 uFlags, HWAVEOUT hDev,
                       WORD wMsg, DWORD dwUser, long dwParam1,
                       long dwParam2)
 {
